ide mixture into 6 portions and shape into patties. Transfer patties onto a plate, cover and place into refrigerator for 20 minutes. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place flour onto a plate and season with extra salt and pepper. Place egg and milk into a bowl and whisk to combine. Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh remaining 80 g panko breadcrumbs into it and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Red cabbage salad"},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh cabbage into it. Add snow peas, cucumber, lime juice, fish sauce and sugar, then stir to combine. Cover and place into refrigerator until ready to serve (see Tips)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chilli mayo"},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh mayonnaise into it. Add hot chilli sauce and stir to combine. Cover and place into refrigerator until ready to serve (see Tips)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Line a plate with paper towel and set aside. Place a large frying pan over medium heat and add oil. Working in batches, coat burger patties in flour, then dip into egg wash and then coat with panko breadcrumbs. Place into frying pan and cook for 4-5 minutes on each side until golden and cooked through. Transfer burgers onto lined plate and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"If desired, preheat the grill and toast bread rolls. To serve, spread rolls with reserved Chilli mayo, then top with a fish burger and Red cabbage salad."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own mayonnaise, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>.","We served our fish burgers atop <i>Mick's ciabatta rolls<\/i> (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip), but you can use any kind of bread rolls or burger buns.","The Red cabbage salad can be stored for up to 3 hours before serving, and the Chilli mayo can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","1h","6 portions"]}